Here, denoising diffusion implicit models (DDIM) (Yang et al., 2023). Here, denoising diffusion implicit models (DDIM) (Song et al., 2021a) form the core of the diffusion framework. In contrast to the denoising diffusion probabilistic models (DDPM) (Ho et al., 2020) originally employed in DreamRec, DDIM provides faster sampling and enhances sampling quality. references:
In general, the four datasets represent different recommendation scenarios, while Amazon TV is more sparse, featuring over 40,000 items. The statistical information is shown in Table 3.
We retain the 20-core datasets and filter out users and items with fewer than twenty interactions except MovieLens, which keeps the original dataset.
Subsequently, we arrange all sequences chronologically and preserve the last 10 interactions as interaction history.
For sequences with less than 10 interactions, we would pad them to 10 with a padding token.
Then, we partition the data into training, validation, and testing sets at an 8:1:1 ratio.
Regarding item text, we utilized GPT to enhance the textual information of the items, except for Amazon TV, which has sufficiently rich text information.
Then, we concatenate the text information of items, including titles, genres, and descriptions, and input them into OpenAI’s TEM text-embeddings-3-small to obtain textual item embeddings. For statistics of datasets, please refer to Table 3.

In general, the four datasets represent different recommendation scenarios, while Amazon TV is more sparse, featuring over 40,000 items. The statistical information is shown in Table 3.
We retain the 20-core datasets and filter out users and items with fewer than twenty interactions except MovieLens, which keeps the original dataset.
Subsequently, we arrange all sequences chronologically and preserve the last 10 interactions as interaction history.
For sequences with less than 10 interactions, we would pad them to 10 with a padding token.
Then, we partition the data into training, validation, and testing sets at an 8:1:1 ratio.
Regarding item text, we utilized GPT to enhance the textual information of the items, except for Amazon TV, which has sufficiently rich text information.
Then, we concatenate the text information of items, including titles, genres, and descriptions, and input them into OpenAI’s TEM text-embeddings-3-small to obtain textual item embeddings. For statistics of datasets, please refer to Table 3.
